**HTML Code for Streaming Video**

Here is a simple HTML file that streams only the video from the specified source. The code includes embedded CSS and JavaScript to create a minimal web app.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>CCTV Live Stream</title>
    <style>
        body {
            margin: 0;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            height: 100vh;
            background-color: black;
        }

        video {
            width: 100%;
            height: auto;
            max-width: 800px;
            border: none;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>
    <video controls autoplay>
        <source src="https://tv.cctv.com/live/" type="application/x-mpegURL">
        Your browser does not support the video tag.
    </video>

    <script>
        const video = document.querySelector('video');
        video.addEventListener('error', function () {
            console.error('Error loading video stream.');
        });
    </script>
</body>

</html>
```

**Key Features of the Code**

- **HTML Structure**: The document is structured with a `<!DOCTYPE html>` declaration, a `head` section for metadata, and a `body` section for content.

- **CSS Styling**: 
  - The body is styled to center the video element both vertically and horizontally.
  - The background color is set to black for a better viewing experience.

- **Video Element**: 
  - The `<video>` tag is used to embed the video stream.
  - The `controls` attribute allows users to control playback.
  - The `autoplay` attribute starts the video automatically.

- **JavaScript Error Handling**: 
  - A simple error event listener is added to log any issues with loading the video stream.

This code can be saved as an HTML file and opened in a web browser to stream the video directly.
